ciational records, newspapers, periodicals, government documents, guidebooks, exhibition catalogues, memoirs, and private letters – Steven C. Soper provides a complex account of Italian liberalism during Europe’s age of association. His study also raises important questions about the role that associations play in emerging democracies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aAssociations, institutions, etcxPolitical aspectszItalyzVenetoxHistory. 0aAssociations, institutions, etczItalyzVenetoxHistoryy19th century. 0aLiberalismzItalyzVenetoxHistoryy19th century. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Italy.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266445640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442664456423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442664456.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK